The National Working Committee (NWC) of the Peopleâ€™s Democratic Party (PDP) has appointed Ali Odefa as Chairman of the reconstituted South-East Zonal Caretaker Committee. The NWC also named Laz Ogbei as Auditor of the committee. Kola Ologbondiyan, National Publicity Secretary, made the announcement on Monday. The spokesman said the action was pursuant to Sections 29 (2)(b) and 31(2)(e) of the PDP Constitution (2017 as amended). The new team will pilot the affairs of the party in the South East for a period not exceeding three months. The NWC enjoined all members to continue to work together in harmony.